I"<<p>From our previous lesson on Resistance, we have used the $\rho$ as a proportionality constant. However, resistivity has a  Resistivity is a measure of the natural property of the material of a given size to resist current. Since it is a natural property, it varies from material to material. The table below shows the resistivity of some common materials.</p>

